Here is a clean, clear, easy explanation for each of the Docker topics you listed.
I’ll write them in simple beginner style + example commands.


---

1) Docker Exec

Used to run a command inside a running container.

Usage

docker exec -it <container_name> <command>

Examples

docker exec -it myapp bash     # open terminal inside container
docker exec -it myapp sh       # for Alpine/BusyBox
docker exec -it myapp ls /app  # list files


---

2) Docker Volumes

Volumes store data outside the container so data does not get deleted.

Create a volume

docker volume create mydata

Use a volume

docker run -v mydata:/var/lib/mysql mysql

List volumes

docker volume ls


---

3) Docker Stats

Real-time resource usage of containers.

Command

docker stats

Shows:

CPU

RAM

Network

Disk I/O



---

4) Docker Build

Used to build an image from a Dockerfile.

Command

docker build -t myimage:latest .


---

5) Docker Multistage Dockerfile

Used to create small, efficient images by using multiple FROM stages.

Example

# Stage 1 - build
FROM golang:1.19 AS builder
WORKDIR /app
COPY . .
RUN go build -o app .

# Stage 2 - final image
FROM alpine:latest
COPY --from=builder /app/app /app/app
CMD ["/app/app"]

Benefits:

Smaller size

Faster deployment

Cleaner layers



---

6) Push Docker Image to Docker Registry

Login

docker login

Tag image

docker tag myapp myusername/myapp:latest

Push image

docker push myusername/myapp:latest


---

7) Docker Scan

Scan image for vulnerabilities.

Command

docker scan myimage


---

8) Push Image to AWS ECR

1. Login to ECR

aws ecr get-login-password --region ap-south-1 \
| docker login --username AWS --password-stdin <account_id>.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com

2. Tag Image

docker tag myapp:latest <account_id>.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/myapp:latest

3. Push Image

docker push <account_id>.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/myapp:latest


---

9) Docker Save & Docker Load

Used for export/import images.

Save image to .tar file

docker save -o myapp.tar myapp:latest

Load image

docker load -i myapp.tar


---

10) Docker Networks

Used for container communication.

Types:

bridge (default)

host

none

overlay (for Swarm)


Create network

docker network create mynetwork

Run container in network

docker run -d --network=mynetwork myapp

List networks

docker network ls


